{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect gNB configuration usage in RU initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_phy_init_RU()` function in the OAI 5G RU initialization code was using a shared configuration (`ru->config`) instead of individual gNB configurations (`ru->gNB_list[n]->gNB_config`) when determining the number of logical antennas. This caused incorrect memory allocation sizes and assertion failures when gNB instances had different antenna configurations.\n\nThis fix modifies the RU initialization to properly iterate through all gNB instances and use their individual configurations to determine the maximum number of logical antennas.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/INIT/nr_init_ru.c`: Changed configuration access from `ru->config` to `ru->gNB_list[n]->gNB_config` in the loop that calculates `nb_log_antennas`.\n- `openair1/PHY/INIT/nr_init_ru.c`: Fixed indentation and spacing issues for better code readability.\n- `openair1/PHY/INIT/nr_init_ru.c`: Corrected typo in log message (\"Feeing\" to \"Freeing\").\n\n"
}